            <div class="rect">
                <div class="before">
                    <h1 class="recthead">Before donation

                    </h1>
                    <p>Donating Blood? Don't take aspirin for 2 days before your appointment.
                        Drink an extra 16 oz. of water (or other nonalcoholic drink) before your appointment.
                        Eat a healthy meal, avoiding fatty foods like hamburgers, fries or ice cream</p>
                </div>
                <div class="during">
                    <h1 class="recthead">During donation</h1>
                    <p>Lie or sit in a reclining chair with your arm extended on an armrest
                        If you have a preference for which arm or vein is used, tell the person who is collecting your blood. 
                        Wear a shirt with sleeves that you can roll up above your elbows.
                        Relax, listen to music, talk to other donors or read while you donate.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="after">
                    <h1 class="recthead">After donation</h1>
                    <p>Do not get immediately after the process is over, rest for at least 5 minutes.
                        If bruising occurs, apply a cold pack to the area periodically during the first 24 hours.
                        Increase your fluid intake for the next 24 to 48 hours as it might take around 24 hours for the body to get the fluids retrieved post blood donation.
                        Eat something that is rich in sugar to boost up your energy levels</p>
                </div>
            </div>


